Data analysis¶

Based on year of 2017, 2019, and 2021. Plus, division between before 2016 and after 2017.

pp_df = pp.to_html()

f = open("df_NoMod.html", "a")  # Expert into html file without modifying any columns in dataset.
f.write(pp_df)
f.close()

# Average annual hours worked        15120
print("\nAverage annual hours worked")
df_AvgAnnHrsWrk = df_sorted_na.loc[
    (df_sorted_na['Indicators'] == 'Average annual hours worked')
]
grouped = df_AvgAnnHrsWrk.groupby(['GEO'])
print(grouped['VALUE'].agg([np.sum, np.mean, np.std, np.size]))
print("The total number of this one is ",len(df_AvgAnnHrsWrk.index))

print("Grabbing the data above 2017.")
df_AvgAnnHrsWrk_above_2017 = df_AvgAnnHrsWrk.loc[
    (df_AvgAnnHrsWrk['REF_DATE'] == 2017) |
    (df_AvgAnnHrsWrk['REF_DATE'] == 2018) |

def provinceConfirmation(df):
    print(df.head(20))
    print(df.info())
    grouped = df.groupby(['Characteristics'])
    print(grouped['VALUE'].agg([np.size]))

f = open("Trial for Alberta.html", "a")  # Expert into html file without modifying any columns in dataset.
f.write(pp_df)
f.close()

print("\nAge group in Ontario")
df_ont_by_age = df_ontario.loc[
    (df_ontario['Characteristics'] == '15 to 24 years') |
    (df_ontario['Characteristics'] == '25 to 34 years') |
    (df_ontario['Characteristics'] == '35 to 44 years') |
    (df_ontario['Characteristics'] == '45 to 54 years') |
    (df_ontario['Characteristics'] == '55 to 64 years') |
    (df_ontario['Characteristics'] == '65 years old and over')]
print(df_ont_by_age.head(20))
grouped = df_ont_by_age.groupby(['Characteristics'])
print(grouped['VALUE'].agg([np.sum, np.size]))
print("The total number of this one is ",len(df_ont_by_age.index))
